One suggestion I would make would be to change `text_to_tensor()` to use the built-in `ord()` function instead of the `np.fromstring()` function. This would simplify the implementation of the function and make it easier to read. Here's the modified `text_to_tensor()` function:

```
@staticmethod
def text_to_tensor(text_batch):
    tensor = torch.zeros(len(text_batch), len(text_batch[0]), dtype=torch.uint8)
    for i, sample in enumerate(text_batch):
